John Alechenu, Abuja The National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party on Wednesday named the Oyo State Governor, Seyi Makinde, as Chairman of its 145 member campaign council for the Ondo State Governorship Election slated for October 10. The council has all the state governors elected under the platform of the party. This was contained in a notice released by the National Publicity Secretary of the PDP, Kola Ologbondiyan, in Abuja. Zamfara State Governor Bello Mattawale was named the deputy chairman of the campaign council. National Financial Secretary of the party, Alhaji Abdullahi Maibashira, was appointed Assistant Secretary of the council.